Svenska Cupen 1941 - Final

Svenska Cupen 1941 was the first season of the main Swedish football Cup. The competition was concluded on 26 October 1941 with the Final, held at Råsunda Stadium, Solna in Stockholms län. Helsingborgs IF won the final 3-1 against IK Sleipner before an attendance of 10,763 spectators.[1]
